gov.usgs.anss.aftac

Class HoldingReport

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.aftac.HoldingReport

  • public class HoldingReport
extends java.lang.Object
    This makes a AftacReport and is called by the AftacHoldingsServer when a command line arrives via a socket connection. The server calls this routine to actually make the report.

    Golden channels on the Ded-AFTAC SNW group:
    1) Build a list of all stations where the SNW group Ded-Aftac is set.
    2) Build a list of channels from all of the holdings or holdingshist where the channel is in the station list and whose 1st channel character is not "A" or "V" and whose second character is [HDWK]
    3) Call addSpans() to read all of the holdings at Golden in the span
    4) addSpans() calls outSpans() which outputs all of the channels on the channel list in WFDISC format.
    DFC channels on NONSEIS_DMC list:
    5) Create a new channel list from the DFC where the sendto NONSEIS_DMC is set.
    6) Call adSpans() for the day in question from the arguments from holdings and holdingshist at DFC.
    7) addSpans calls outSpans() which outputs all of the channels on the channel list if WFDISC format. 

         -s stationRegExp The station regular express in NSCL order
     -b begindate Can be all, for yyyy,ddd-hh:mm:ss or yyyy/mm/dd-hh:mm:ss
     -e enddate Same form as begindate
     -d duration nnnnn[dD] assumed seconds unless "d" is present
